# Pin Windows batch files to CRLF line endings.
#
# cmd.exe is mostly tolerant of LF but specifically breaks `goto :label`
# jumps and parenthesised `if/else` blocks when given LF-only files —
# the script silently exits part-way through.  We had a real outage
# (start.cmd appearing to "work" for the Claude block then never
# running the Gemini probe or the launch) traced to this exact issue.
#
# Pinning these to CRLF keeps Linux / macOS git checkouts from
# normalising to LF on commit, and Windows checkouts from getting
# LF-only content via gitconfig core.autocrlf=input.
*.cmd text eol=crlf
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.ps1 text eol=crlf
